<div id="header">

<p>
<h2>The most important part of a software bug's life is triage.</h2>
</p>
</div>

<div id="leftside">

<p>
Triage is the most important and least loved part of a bug's lifecycle, and
Mozilla sees dozens or hundreds of new bugs filed every day.
</p>

<p>
iIf you can spare a few minutes per day you can help us fight back the tide. 
Sign up below; enter your name, Bugzilla email address, and a maximum number
of bugs we can send you.  
</p>

<p>
Once a week, five days a week or every day if you like, we'll send you an email 
with links to new issues our community is facing so you can help get them 
to the right place and the right person with the right information.
</p>

<p>
<form action="index.py" method="post">
Name or IRC handle: <input type="text" name="nickname"/><br/>
Email: <input type="text" name="email" /><br/>
Number of bugs:
<select name="number">
<option value="1">1</option>
<option value="2">2</option>
<option value="3">3</option>
<option value="5">5</option>
<option value="8">8</option>
<option value="12">12</option>
<option value="15">15</option>
</select><br/>
How often? 
<select name="rate">
<option value="daily">Daily</option>
<option value="workdays">Mon-Fri</option>
<option value="weekly">Weekly</option>
</select>
</p>
<p>
 <input type="submit" value="Submit"></p>
</form>
</p>
</div>


<div id="rightside">
<p>
We're also updating Bugzilla to make sorting new bugs into new categories fast
and easy. Soon moving bugs to a new category will be a matter of a few seconds 
and one step. 
</p>
<p>
We can even simplify the triage process with 
<a href="https://github.com/gijsk/triage-helper">the Triage-Helper addon</a>. 
This will let triagers quickly ask contributors for a series of common next 
steps, including reproducing the bug in a clean profile or safe mode, 
narrowing down a test case, and others.
</p>
<p>
If you're just getting started: Welcome! You'll need a Bugzilla account with <a href="https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/page.cgi?id=get_permissions.html">"CanConfirm"</a> 
permissions to help. Once you have those, please take a moment to read these
documents on <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/QA/Triaging_Bugs_for_Firefox">Effective
bug triage for Firefox</a> and best practices for <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/QA/Confirming_unconfirmed_bugs">confirm
unconfirmed bugs</a>.
</p>
</div>



